learning_outcomes.en:
Upon completion the course, a student will:
- obtain thorough knowledge about the underlying principles of project management;
- understand the rules of project management and be able to analyse these in the context of implementation of specific measures;
- acquire sufficient training for writing projects, implementing them. and reporting on activities and human resources;
- be skilful in evaluating different projects;
- familiarize with the compilation of a project budget and put together a working schedule;
- be able to understand the importance of a project to funders and other interested parties;
- familiarize with EU and national funding programs and be able to search for suitable funding source for the project idea.

learning_outcomes.et:
Kursuse edukalt läbinu:
- orienteerub projekti finantseerimise siseriiklikes ja EL meetmetes ning omab teadmisi sobiva rahastamisallika otsinguks;
- tunneb projektide koostamise, tellimise ja juhtimise põhialuseid;
- omab praktilisi oskusi projekti kirjutamiseks ja tellimiseks.

description.et:
All positively assessed homeworks worth half of the maximum grade (A). The project proposal will be assessed from D to A, based on the following criteria: 
D - the form is in compliance with the requirements and, in general, correct; data is minimal, but relevant; the argumentation is understandable, but at times insecure; the written assignment and its presentation is logical and associated;
C - the form is in compliance with the requirements and correct; data is relevant and sufficient; interpretations are logical and there is certainty in creating connections; the treatment of the project idea is logical, but there are weaknesses with logical framework; the written assignment and its presentation is logical and well associated;
B - the form is excellent; the choice, amount and seection of data is very good; thorough analysis of logical framework and its parts; bold interpretation based on connections; the project application as a whole is logical and smooth;
A - the written form and its presentation is excellent; the choice, amount and selection of data is well mixed with the convincing explanations; the depth of the analysis and the level of independent interpretation is remarkable; the connections are thorough-going and creative; the treatment of the subject is innovative and logical; the project application is a remarkable achievement on the whole.
